  planner_response {
    thinking: "**Considering Key Implementation**\n\nI\'ve clarified the Google Maps Platform skill\'s key dependency: an API key triggers the splash screen if missing. Now, I\'m pivoting to the \"Milk Tea / Drinker\'s Compass\" idea. Geolocation and device orientation are essential, but the API key is not a key component in my current implementation. I am considering different ways to get location and device orientation, without Google Maps.\n\n\n**Refining Map Integration**\n\nI\'m now focusing on map integration and thinking how to integrate map services, with a focus on a free option, for the Milk Tea Compass app. A Google Maps API key would unlock its full potential, but a seamless Leaflet integration is my current top priority as a zero-friction fallback. Leaflet integration would be the default, ensuring that the app is functional right out of the box, even without configuration. This offers a more accessible experience!\n\n\n**Visualizing Dynamic Compass**\n\nI\'m now diving into the aesthetic and interactive aspects of the \"Milk Tea/Alcoholic Compass\". I envision a dynamic, rotating compass, either reflecting real-time heading or controlled by a manual dial. This compass will point towards the nearest shop, displaying distance and angle. I\'m excited about the radar visualization, using either custom Canvas or React SVG, and considering soft, themed visuals for each mode.\n\n\n**Designing Thematic Modes**\n\nI\'m now fully immersed in the design details, refining the themed modes. The \"Drinker Mode\" is shaping up with a cyberpunk aesthetic: neon violet and green, glowing cocktail glasses, and a sonar-like radar sweep to locate pubs and bars. The \"\346\230\276\347\244\272\350\267\235\347\246\273\" (Display Distance) is my next focus, with real-time distance calculations using the Haversine formula from user\'s location to shops, whether real or simulated.\n\n\n"
    modified_response: "I will view the `gemini-api` skill instructions to ensure we properly utilize the server-side Gemini API if we want to fetch realistic or real places near any coordinates."
    thinking_duration {
      seconds: 5
      nanos: 940898747
    }
    stop_reason: STOP_REASON_STOP_PATTERN
  }
}
