  planner_response {
    thinking: "**Considering Shop Locations**\n\nI\'m now focusing on creating static mock shops and a dynamic shop generator at `/src/data/mockShops.ts`. I\'m questioning the need for a dynamic generator. It seems necessary because a user\'s location, whether Chengdu, Paris, or New York, determines their specific latitude and longitude. The generator needs to handle these varying locations and populate shop data accordingly.\n\n\n**Confirming Dynamic Generation Necessity**\n\nI\'ve determined the dynamic shop generator is essential. Hardcoding locations, like Beijing, creates absurd distances (8,000 km!). The generator will use user coordinates (real or simulated) to create 5 milk tea and 5 bar shops within 150-1200m. Shop names will be realistically localized (e.g., Mixue Ice Cream & Tea). I\'ll also add presets for famous locations like Chengdu Chunxi Road, ensuring local distances and a functional compass.\n\n\n**Implementing Distance Utilities**\n\nI\'m now implementing distance and bearing calculations. I\'ve written the Haversine formula for distance in meters and the `getBearing` function to determine the absolute angle from the user to a target. These utilities will be crucial for the shop generator to place locations accurately relative to the user\'s location.\n\n\n**Defining Shop Characteristics**\n\nI\'m now focusing on defining shop characteristics to populate the shop generator. I\'m creating lists of milk tea brands and bar types, complete with realistic signatures, price ranges, ratings, and relevant tags. I\'m focusing on \"\350\234\234\351\233\252\345\206\260\345\237\216,\" \"\345\226\234\350\214\266,\" \"\351\234\270\347\216\213\350\214\266\345\247\254,\" and \"\350\214\266\351\242\234\346\202\246\350\211\262\" as my milk tea brands, thinking through their individual styles.\n\n\n"
    modified_response: "I will create `/src/data/mockShops.ts` containing our list of Chinese city presets (for simulator testing), distance/bearing calculation utilities, and a dynamic local shop generator. The generator creates highly customized, realistic, and mathematically consistent coordinates near any position (real GPS or preset) so the compass always has nearby locations to point to."
    thinking_duration {
      seconds: 7
      nanos: 803325996
    }
    stop_reason: STOP_REASON_STOP_PATTERN
  }
