    thinking: "**Creating Radar Visualization**\n\nI\'ve completed `/src/components/Compass.tsx` - I\'m very happy with how polished and comprehensive it is! I\'m now starting on `/src/components/Radar.tsx`. I\'m trying to decide on what visual form to build the \"Bar Radar and Milk Tea Radar\" in.\n\n\n**Designing Radar Functionality**\n\nI\'m now diving into the core functionality. I\'m choosing between Canvas and SVG for the radar display. I am prioritizing a dynamic, visual experience: pulsing dots, a sweeping line that interacts with blips, and interactive blip selection, with realistic range labels on the concentric rings. I\'m focusing on the math for plotting shop positions in polar coordinates. I want the radar to be customizable with a visual theme!\n\n\n**Calculating Radar Coordinates**\n\nI\'ve worked out the coordinate calculations for plotting blips on the radar! I\'m now confident in the core math. With a maximum range of 1000m, and the center of the canvas at (cx, cy) with radius R, the ratio of a shop\'s distance and bearing determine its x and y coordinates. The sweep functionality is straightforward: keeping a `sweepAngle` state that is drawn as a line from the center to its circumference!\n\n\n"
    modified_response: "I will create `/src/components/Radar.tsx`. This component implements a fully functional Sonar/Radar sweep using an HTML `<canvas>` and a high-performance `requestAnimationFrame` animation loop. In \"Milk Tea Mode\" (\345\245\266\350\214\266\351\233\267\350\276\276), it displays sweet bubble tea pink grids with floating boba balls as blips; in \"Drinker Mode\" (\351\205\222\351\246\206\351\233\267\350\276\276), it mimics a glowing tactical green/violet sonar grid. It displays the distance rings (200m, 500m, 1000m) and illuminates the blips with a decaying trailing glow as the radar sweep line passes across their angular bearing. Users can click on blips to select/lock a shop."
    thinking_duration {
      seconds: 4
