  planner_response {
    thinking: "**Considering Map Styling**\n\nI\'m now focusing on `/src/components/MapContainer.tsx`. I need to figure out how to make Leaflet aesthetically pleasing and thematically consistent. I\'m exploring stylish map tile providers as a solution, moving away from the standard OpenStreetMap tiles. A more modern aesthetic is the goal.\n\n\n**Implementing Dynamic Map Themes**\n\nI\'ve decided to integrate CartoDB Positron and Dark Matter tile sets. These minimalist styles are perfect for Milk Tea and Drinker modes, respectively. I\'m excited about dynamically switching between them based on the application\'s current mode. I\'m focusing on the React implementation, including the `mapRef` and the `useEffect` hook for map initialization. It\'s a elegant solution.\n\n\n**Designing Custom Map Markers**\n\nI\'ve hit upon a game-changing marker solution! Standard Leaflet markers are prone to errors, but using `L.divIcon` allows for bulletproof, visually stunning custom markers styled with Tailwind CSS. My plan is: user markers will be pulsating blue/pink circles with a white core, milk tea shops will feature a pink circle with a bouncing \360\237\247\213 emoji, and bars will have a glowing violet circle with a \360\237\215\270 emoji.\nI\'m now detailing `/src/components/MapContainer.tsx`, especially map div, and implementing map view center and bounds updates, dependent on `userLocation` or `shops` changes.\n\n\n"
    modified_response: "I will create `/src/components/MapContainer.tsx` to display our interactive map. It uses dynamic custom styling for high design quality:\n1. **Dynamic Theme Styling**: In \"Milk Tea Mode\", it renders the **CartoDB Positron** light map theme. In \"Drinker Mode\", it switches to **CartoDB Dark Matter** dark map theme.\n2. **Interactive Teleportation**: Users can click/tap anywhere on the map to \"teleport\" their simulated position. The app instantly updates nearby shops and re-orients the compass relative to that new location.\n3. **SVG/Tailwind Custom Markers**: Avoids brittle default marker assets by rendering custom Leaflet `L.divIcon` elements styled with Tailwind, showing pulsating circles and custom emojis (`\360\237\247\213` and `\360\237\215\271`) that match the chosen theme.\n4. **Dynamic Navigation Paths**: Draws a visual polyline connecting the user\'s location directly to their locked destination."
    thinking_duration {
      seconds: 4
      nanos: 517583207
    }
    stop_reason: STOP_REASON_STOP_PATTERN
  }
}
