  planner_response {
    thinking: "**Analyzing Mobile Sensor Issues**\n\nI\'m now diving into the reasons mobile compass and gyroscope features become unavailable, and exploring methods for both repair and optimization. The initial focus is on the security protocols implemented on iOS and Android devices, particularly the stringent access rules browsers enforce on sensor APIs. It\'s good to know that the dev URL already satisfies the HTTPS requirement.\n\n\n**Addressing IFrame Restrictions**\n\nI\'ve hit a key point: our application, running in an IFrame, by default lacks device orientation and gyroscope permissions. Even with HTTPS, `SecurityError` or `PermissionDenied` crops up when using `DeviceOrientationEvent.requestPermission` within the IFrame, unless the parent grants `allow` attribute. This renders `sensorStatus` as `unavailable`. I\'m now exploring solutions like prompting users to run independently in such scenarios. Also, I\'m studying the user gesture requirement in iOS 13+ that is directly associated with the click event, and the Android Chrome `deviceorientationabsolute` event.\n\n\n**Optimizing Event Handling**\n\nI\'m now implementing a multi-event listening strategy. I\'ll be listening for both `deviceorientation` and `deviceorientationabsolute` events, giving preference to `deviceorientationabsolute` on Android and Chrome devices for a more accurate physical orientation reading. Additionally, I\'m working on robust calculation logic that gracefully handles different compass heading properties. I\'m also planning to enhance the user experience with more intuitive error and status messages.\n\n\n**Refining Sensor Logic**\n\nI\'m now revising the sensor-listening components in `/src/App.tsx` to fully support `deviceorientationabsolute` events, while also gracefully detecting IFrame sandbox restrictions. My aim is to deliver user-friendly guidance. I\'m focusing on the `handleOrientation` and `requestDeviceOrientation` functions, ensuring that heading calculations are robust. This is coupled with user-focused error handling.\n\n\n"
    thinking_duration {
      seconds: 17
      nanos: 457064539
    }
    stop_reason: STOP_REASON_STOP_PATTERN
  }
}
